We recommended that Management strictly adhere to the mandates of COA Circular 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012, COA Circular 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014 and RA 10121 (PDRRM), specifically on accounting and reporting of LDRRMF such as the following:
9. proper preparation of LDRRMF Plan and Budget; 
10. strict adherence by it in the utilization of the DRRMF, copy furnished the COA; 
11. maintaining a separate Registry for Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (RAAO) for LDRRMF, namely, RAAO – for QRF, RAAO – for MOOE and RAAO – for CO; 
12. rendering a monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF, copy furnished the COA; and 
13. ensuring that all unexpended/unobligated balance of the QRF and LDRRMF-MOOE are transferred to the Special Trust Fund under the account “Trust Liability – DRRM” (Code 438) in the Trust Funds books.

We recommended that the LGU should strictly enforce the provisions of the New Government Accounting System (NGAS) Manual for LGUs and the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standard (PPSAS), in particular to Sections 114 and 124 of the Manual and PPSAS 17 which mandates the following:
A. the chief accountant should maintain PPE Ledger Card for each category of PPE. Such ledger cards should contain the details of the PPE account in the inventory control account in the general ledger;
B. the general services officer (GSO) or the municipal treasurer, as the case maybe, should maintain stock cards and property cards for supplies and PPE to account for the receipt and disposition of the same and, that,, the balance per stock card / property cards should always reconcile with the ledger cards of the accounting unit and other property records like Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE);
C. the local chief executive should cause for the conduct of physical count of PPE annually and the preparation of the annual Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) which has to be submitted to the concerned Auditor not later than January 31 of each year; and
D. infrastructure assets should be recognized in the books of accounts as PPE so that assets recorded in the registry of public infrastructures should then be brought back to the books to start in the year 2016.

